# Clerk UserProfile — Custom Pages & Links

Extend `<UserProfile />` via `<UserButton />` sub-components to add custom pages (e.g. App Settings) to the profile sidenav. This project uses `<UserButton />` in modal mode (the default), so always use `<UserButton.UserProfilePage />` and `<UserButton.UserProfileLink />`.

## Adding a Custom Page

All props (`label`, `labelIcon`, `url`, `children`) are **required**.

```tsx
import { UserButton } from "@clerk/nextjs";

<UserButton>
  <UserButton.UserProfilePage label="App Settings" labelIcon={<SettingsIcon />} url="app-settings">
    <AppSettingsPage />
  </UserButton.UserProfilePage>
</UserButton>
```

## Adding a Custom Link

```tsx
<UserButton>
  <UserButton.UserProfileLink label="Homepage" labelIcon={<HomeIcon />} url="/" />
</UserButton>
```

## Reordering Default Routes

Target built-in pages with `label="account"` or `label="security"` to reposition them. The first item **cannot** be a custom link.

```tsx
<UserButton>
  <UserButton.UserProfilePage label="App Settings" labelIcon={<SettingsIcon />} url="app-settings">
    <AppSettingsPage />
  </UserButton.UserProfilePage>
  <UserButton.UserProfilePage label="account" />
  <UserButton.UserProfilePage label="security" />
</UserButton>
```

## Rules

- Use `<UserButton.UserProfilePage />` — never `<UserProfile.Page />` (project uses modal mode)
- Use `<UserButton.UserProfileLink />` — never `<UserProfile.Link />`
- All four props (`label`, `labelIcon`, `url`, `children`) are required for custom pages
- All three props (`label`, `labelIcon`, `url`) are required for custom links
- Extract page content into its own component — never inline large JSX as children
- The first sidenav item cannot be a custom link when reordering
- Custom page components must be Client Components (`"use client"`) if they use hooks or interactivity
